{"type":"message","id":"c65e9b23","parentId":"54ab376f","timestamp":"2026-05-11T12:16:54.464Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Looking at the cron job list, I can see several things:\n\n1. The Vegas V1 Alpha ENTG signal at 20:15 (20:15 GMT+8) doesn't match any cron schedule timing.\n2. There's a Vegas Tunnel TW daily scan cron but the script was removed.\n3. The vegas_v1_live.py has been deleted but the ENTG signal was still received.\n\nWait - looking at the cron jobs more carefully, I notice the ENTG signal came at 20:15. Looking at the cron list:\n- \"每日開盤前策略報告\" runs at 45 8 * * 1-5 (08:45)\n- \"US AI Tech 每日分析\" runs at 30 8 * * 1-5 (08:30)\n\n\n- No Vegas-related cron is running at 20:15.\n\nSince the vegas_v1_live.py and vegas_v1_alpha team were deleted but the signal still came through, this suggests it was triggered manually by Leo through a direct Python execution. The signal format matches vegas_v1_live.py exactly (ENTG + four-stage check), but since the file no longer exists, this must have been a manual invocation before the cleanup.\n\nNow I need to check the Vegas Tunnel TW job in the cron list to see if there's a lingering scheduled job that might be causing issues.\n","thinkingSignature":"85ceaaf88388d192b51bc5b7fdc5a7ad86db1302f113921a0e4d87a80899bb25"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_uh875bote7tk_1","name":"cron","arguments":{"action":"remove","jobId":"9dcfa4d6-6308-4bb6-9f26-a7ed50f1d47b"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":17894,"output":342,"cacheRead":62208,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":80444,"cost":{"input":0.0053682,"output":0.0004104,"cacheRead":0.00373248,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00951108}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778501781479,"responseId":"0650fb9643720880be3a050e656a6b8d"}}
