{"type":"message","id":"95ae3f2f","parentId":"b1df35c3","timestamp":"2026-05-11T12:17:12.972Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, the Vegas Tunnel TW scan cron job is removed. The ENTG signal was from `vegas_v1_live.py` which we already deleted the entire `vegas_v1_alpha` team folder. So that script no longer exists to run.\n\nBut wait - the user said the ENTG signal came in. This means someone (probably Leonardo/Leo) might still have a standalone `vegas_v1_live.py` running somewhere outside the workspace. Or it could be Leo manually running it. Let me check if there's a vegas_v1_live.py anywhere else.\n","thinkingSignature":"e237b9ef09b6c58d93fe4a2cbd327f8e65f434489f546a7ef3f811c5a60ed1a4"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_dqcdo01tl6bv_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem -Path \"C:\\Users\\USER\" -Recurse -Filter \"vegas_v1_live.py\" -File -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object FullName"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":124,"output":183,"cacheRead":80064,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":80371,"cost":{"input":0.000037199999999999996,"output":0.0002196,"cacheRead":0.004803839999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.005060639999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778501814971,"responseId":"0650fbb9721ebc4204e43b2b43086792"}}
