{"type":"message","id":"5970fc34","parentId":"33515352","timestamp":"2026-05-11T12:22:19.585Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Jo is asking me to investigate why Leo would manually trigger this signal and how to prevent it. But the vegas_v1_alpha team folder was already deleted. Let me check if there's any remaining path or alias that could still run vegas_v1_live.py. Also, Jo sent this from Telegram and the message came through Ray's session. \n\nThe key question is: where is Leo's bot token and chat ID configured, and is there any remaining trigger mechanism?\n\nActually, I think Jo is asking about the Telegram bot itself - the bot token \"872054…qAiY\" that was hardcoded in vegas_v1_live.py. Even though the script was deleted, if the bot token is still active, someone could have re-created the script or be running it from elsewhere.\n\n\nI need to systematically search through all the workspaces and agent directories to see if vegas_v1_live.py has been recreated or if there's another version of it running under a different name that Jo might be executing manually.\n","thinkingSignature":"e8d8328edffecde20ad726095ad342a1dd08dfc641c51df57cf00c9ac24758c3"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_zpmssp92ezx2_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem -Path \"C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\workspace\" -Recurse -File -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Where-Object { $_.Name -match \"vegas|v1_live|leonardo\" } | Select-Object FullName"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":6130,"output":285,"cacheRead":61760,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":68175,"cost":{"input":0.001839,"output":0.00034199999999999996,"cacheRead":0.0037056,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0058866}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778502120336,"responseId":"0650fcead33dba09084f8b4e2aeac262"}}
