{"type":"message","id":"97e7ad1b","parentId":"de89160a","timestamp":"2026-05-11T19:07:03.369Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The model returned JSON but with markdown code block formatting around it (` ```json ... ``` `). The `sanitize_llm_output` function should handle this, but the raw response still has the markdown. Let me fix the tina_bridge to strip markdown code blocks before JSON parsing.\n\nAlso the response got cut off - it seems like the model response was truncated mid-JSON. The error says \"Invalid control character\" which means the response had newlines/control characters embedded in it.\n\nLet me fix tina_bridge.py to properly handle the markdown-wrapped JSON responses.\n","thinkingSignature":"e34d80877dd05876d9d91037bc19a86a613759aeb14abbc0002fc9e0057dca90"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\n模型輸出了 Markdown 包裝的 JSON（` ```json ... ``` `），需要清理。修正一下：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_mc0re77lwbd6_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\\ray\\tina_bridge.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":581,"output":180,"cacheRead":105856,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":106617,"cost":{"input":0.00017429999999999998,"output":0.000216,"cacheRead":0.0063513599999999995,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.006741659999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778526412576,"responseId":"06515bce88ae283bebe8816770f6e3b3"}}
{"type":"message","id":"639a2fe6","parentId":"97e7ad1b","timestamp":"2026-05-11T19:07:03.378Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_mc0re77lwbd6_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-\n\"\"\"\nRay Tina Bridge - Ollama Local Model Integration Layer\nCompatible with OpenClaw Agent workspace\n\nUsage:\n  from tina_bridge import TinaBridge\n  bridge = TinaBridge(model=\"qwen2.5:1.5b\")\n  result = bridge.ask_logic(\"提煉買入策略\", context_data)\n\"\"\"\n\nimport requests\nimport json\nfrom typing import Optional, Dict\n\nDEFAULT_URL   = \"http://localhost:11434/api/chat\"  # Ollama native API\nDEFAULT_MODEL = \"qwen2.5:1.5b\"\n\n\nclass TinaBridge:\n    \"\"\"\n    Sends quant logic requests to local Qwen via Ollama.\n    NL2Code validation ensures stable JSON output.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, model: str = DEFAULT_MODEL, base_url: str = DEFAULT_URL):\n        self.url   = base_url\n        self.model = model\n\n    def ask_logic(self, prompt: str, context_data: str = \"\") -> str:\n        \"\"\"\n        Send task to local Qwen, return JSON string.\n        Returns error JSON on failure.\n        \"\"\"\n        system_prompt = (\n            \"You are Ray's quant logic unit. Tina Architecture Edition. \"\n            \"Always output valid JSON. No natural language. \"\n            \"Schema: {\\\"strategy_name\\\":\\\"...\\\",\\\"indicator\\\":\\\"...\\\",\"\n            \"\\\"params\\\":{},\\\"entry_condition\\\":{},\\\"stop_loss\\\":0.0}\"\n        )\n\n        payload = {\n            \"model\":     self.model,\n            \"messages\": [\n                {\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": system_prompt},\n                {\"role\": \"user\",   \"content\": f\"Context:\\n{context_data}\\n\\nTask:\\n{prompt}\"}\n            ],\n            \"temperature\": 0.1,\n            \"stream\":     False,\n        }\n\n        try:\n            resp = requests.post(self.url, json=payload, timeout=120)\n            resp.raise_for_status()\n            content = resp.json()[\"message\"][\"content\"]\n            json.loads(content)  # validate\n            return content\n\n        except requests.exceptions.ConnectionError:\n            return '{\"error\": \"Ollama not running\", \"details\": \"Start ollama serve\"}'\n        except json.JSONDecodeError:\n            return f'{{\"error\": \"Invalid JSON from model\", \"details\": \"{content[:200]}\"}}'\n        except Exception as e:\n            return f'{{\"error\": \"Bridge failure\", \"details\": \"{str(e)}\"}}'\n\n    def batch_ask(self, tasks: list) -> list:\n        \"\"\"Batch query multiple tasks.\"\"\"\n        return [self.ask_logic(t[\"prompt\"], t.get(\"context\", \"\")) for t in tasks]\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    bridge = TinaBridge()\n    data = \"Stock: NVDA | RSI: 28 | Foreign Net Buy: +5000 | Sharpe: 1.8 | MDD: 0.08 | WinRate: 55%\"\n    result = bridge.ask_logic(\"輸出嚴格 JSON 策略\", data)\n    print(result)\n    parsed = json.loads(result)\n    print(f\"Strategy: {parsed.get('strategy_name', 'N/A')}\")"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1778526423378}}
{"type":"message","id":"ae992457","parentId":"639a2fe6","timestamp":"2026-05-11T19:07:17.315Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is that the model's JSON output contains newlines and the Python `json.loads()` is failing because of control characters in the JSON string (the raw `\\n` characters aren't escaped). I need to handle this more carefully in the bridge. Let me update the bridge to handle JSON with newlines.\n\nThe problem is that `json.loads(content)` is failing when the content has literal newlines that aren't properly escaped in the JSON. Actually looking at the error: `Invalid control character at: line 1 column 57 (char 56)` - this suggests the model is outputting JSON with literal newlines inside the string value (e.g., `\\n` not escaped as `\\\\n`). \n\nThe raw content is `{\"strategy_name\": \"Tina Architecture Edition\", \"indicator\": {\"RSI\": 28, ...}, \"entry_condition\": {\"Long_Entr\"...}` with actual newlines embedded. The `json.loads()` in Python is strict about newlines inside JSON strings - they must be escaped as `\\n`.\n \nI'll sanitize the JSON by replacing literal newlines with escaped `\\n` characters before attempting to parse it, so the model can output formatted JSON and the bridge can still validate it.\n","thinkingSignature":"a3a9e2acde3b773ad5fa0fa46ea39020c1de79cadc183b33e0e0a4be021ade78"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6vvik7s3w9la_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cmd /c 'cd /d \"C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\\ray\" && powershell -Command \"(Get-Content tina_bridge.py -Raw)\" | Select-Object -First 5","timeout":"10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":730,"output":324,"cacheRead":106432,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":107486,"cost":{"input":0.00021899999999999998,"output":0.00038879999999999996,"cacheRead":0.00638592,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00699372}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778526423385,"respons