{"type":"message","id":"961c4618","parentId":"5f2e6829","timestamp":"2026-05-11T19:29:12.444Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_u8pmayr6umes_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"NVDA: price=219.29, math_passed=True\r\nSharpe=6.43, MDD=0.096, WinRate=0.7\r\n\r\n1.5B Output:\r\n{\r\n  \"error\": \"NL2Code rejected: entry_condition missing 'operator'\",\r\n  \"raw\": \"{\\n    \\\"strategy_name\\\":\\\"FastLogicUnit\\\",\\n    \\\"indicator\\\":\\\"RSI, KDJ J, Mom 5D\\\",\\n    \\\"params\\\":{\\n        \\\"EMA20\\\":203.27,\\n        \\\"EMA60\\\":192.91\\n    },\\n    \\\"entry_condition\\\":{},\\n    \\\"stop_loss\\\":0.0\\n}\"\r\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":7601,"aggregated":"NVDA: price=219.29, math_passed=True\r\nSharpe=6.43, MDD=0.096, WinRate=0.7\r\n\r\n1.5B Output:\r\n{\r\n  \"error\": \"NL2Code rejected: entry_condition missing 'operator'\",\r\n  \"raw\": \"{\\n    \\\"strategy_name\\\":\\\"FastLogicUnit\\\",\\n    \\\"indicator\\\":\\\"RSI, KDJ J, Mom 5D\\\",\\n    \\\"params\\\":{\\n        \\\"EMA20\\\":203.27,\\n        \\\"EMA60\\\":192.91\\n    },\\n    \\\"entry_condition\\\":{},\\n    \\\"stop_loss\\\":0.0\\n}\"\r\n}","cwd":"C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\\ray"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778527752443}}
{"type":"message","id":"8237eda7","parentId":"961c4618","timestamp":"2026-05-11T19:29:38.776Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The validator isn't returning the \"corrected\" dict when there are \"corrections\". The issue is that corrections (like indicator 'RSI, KDJ J, Mom 5D' -> 'MOMENTUM' and strategy_name -> 'FASTLOGICUNIT') happen during validation but when `is_valid=False` and corrections exist, we do `if corrected: result = corrected`. But `corrected` is the fixed dict (which should have the corrections applied). Let me debug this.\n\nActually looking at the validation code more carefully:\n\n```python\nif ind:\n    normalized = _normalize_indicator(ind)\n    if normalized:\n        if ind != normalized:\n            self.corrections.append(f\"indicator '{ind}' -> '{normalized}'\")\n        axiom[\"indicator\"] = normalized  # <-- modifies axiom in place!\n    elif self.auto_correct:\n        axiom[\"indicator\"] = \"MOMENTUM\"\n```\n\nSo `axiom[\"indicator\"]` IS being updated. And at the end:\n```python\nis_valid = len(self.errors) == 0\nreturn is_valid, axiom if is_valid else None, self.errors\n```\n\nSo when `is_valid=False` but `axiom` was modified (with corrections), we return `None` for axiom. That's the bug - we should return the axiom even on validation failure if it was auto-corrected.\n\nBut I'm returning `None` for the axiom when `is_valid=False`. The actual return is `axiom if is_valid else None`. So if the name and indicator were auto-corrected but there are still errors (like missing entry_condition), `corrected` is `None` and we return an error.\n\nThe fix: don't return `None` for corrected dict with corrections. Let me update the validator to return the corrected dict even on failure if corrections were applied.\n","thinkingSignature":"aaabee04d270b5136cf93dd2a353e4828bd5fceeda73f8cc2bbae0b3344ac26e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_t9qatvhy5mrj_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"with open('ray_nl2code.py', 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n    content = f.read()\n\nold = '''        is_valid = len(self.errors) == 0\n        return is_valid, axiom if is_valid else None, self.errors'''\n\nnew = '''        is_valid = len(self.errors) == 0\n        # 即使验证失败，如果有自动修正，仍返回修正后的 dict\n        if not is_valid and self.corrections and axiom:\n            return False, axiom, self.errors\n        return is_valid, axiom if is_valid else None, self.errors'''\n\nif old in content:\n    content = content.replace(old, new)\n    with open('ray_nl2code.py', 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n        f.write(content)\n    print(\"Fixed validator to return corrected dict\")\nelse:\n    print(\"Pattern not found\")","path":"C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\\ray\\fix_nl2code.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":272,"output":611,"cacheRead":152000,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":152883,"cost":{"input":0.00008159999999999999,"output":0.0007331999999999999,"cacheRead":0.00912,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.009934799999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778527752449,"responseId":"06516110b37bb016a532c2bbe1afb865"}}
