{"type":"message","id":"8d001254","parentId":"bad8e1b9","timestamp":"2026-05-11T19:54:00.787Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the current session is `agent:ray:telegram:direct:1616824689`. So Jo is talking to Ray (this agent). The Vegas signal messages (MCHP, ENTG) came from somewhere else - they weren't from Ray.\n\nLet me think about this more carefully. The message metadata shows:\n- `sender_label: \"Ray\"` - meaning the sender's label in this conversation IS \"Ray\" (the agent itself)\n- The body contains the Vegas signal in the \"🚀 Vegas V1 Alpha 進場訊號\" format\n\nWait - `sender_label: \"Ray\"` means the message was sent by the Ray agent. This is confusing because it means the Ray agent sent those Vegas signals. But in the conversation, I'm Ray, so maybe these messages are from the current session itself?\n \nI'm trying to trace where these Vegas signals originate. The `vegas_v1_live.py` file was deleted, so there's no clear source for these messages. The cron job wasn't the trigger, and there's no evidence of Leo manually executing it either. The messages appear to come from the Ray agent itself, but there's no clear mechanism for how it would be sending these specific signals.\n\nThe `sender_label: \"Ray\"` indicates these are incoming messages from the Ray session, not outgoing ones. This suggests the Ray agent generated these Vegas signals internally, even though the source code no longer exists. It's possible the messages were produced through some automated process within the Ray agent, but the exact origin remains unclear. I'm realizing the distinction between the Telegram message metadata and the chat history here. The `sender_label: \"Ray\"` in the conversation context indicates these messages came through the Ray agent's Telegram account, but that doesn't necessarily mean Ray is actively generating them—it could be that messages are being routed through Ray's session from another source like Leo.\n\nLooking at the message content itself, the Vegas V1 Alpha format with the four-stage check is exactly what Leo's system produces, so these messages might actually be forwarded through Ray's channel rather than originated by Ray. The session history would clarify whether Ray is executing this logic or just passing these messages along from Leonardo's system. Looking at the message context more carefully, the Vegas V1 Alpha signal format is very distinctive and matches exactly what Leo's `vegas_v1_live.py` script would generate. Since that script has been deleted and the Vegas cron job is gone, the only remaining possibility is that Leo is sending these signals directly through the Telegram chat - either manually or through some external process that bypasses the cron system entirely.\n\nThe source is almost certainly Leonardo's Telegram bot, which has the `@LeoTradeBot` token hardcoded in the script. This means Jo is receiving direct notifications from Leo's system rather than through any scheduled automation.\n","thinkingSignature":"830f6a297583945904cd723fd8799c4bdfddbbafd11a49f68927e9d80ffa54a4"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_axn607nlepjn_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem -Path \"C:\\Users\\USER\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\" -Recurse -File -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Where-Object { $_.Name -match \"telegram|channel|forward\" } | Select-Object FullName"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":884,"output":652,"cacheRead":89280,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":90816,"cost":{"input":0.0002652,"output":0.0007823999999999999,"cacheRead":0.005356799999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.006404399999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778502230367,"responseId":"0650fd57866a885e623b0ec82f72f79a"}}
