{"type":"message","id":"61ca4a62","parentId":"d7fd44d6","timestamp":"2026-05-11T19:54:00.787Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `leo_autonomous_develop.py` is also a standalone analysis script that produces JSON files, not Telegram messages. It doesn't send messages to Telegram.\n\nLet me look at all Python scripts in the entire workspace and search for the exact message format \"🚀 Vegas V1 Alpha 進場訊號\".\n\nActually, let me think about this differently. The message format is \"🚀 Vegas V1 Alpha 進場訊號\". This is sent by `send_telegram()` in `vegas_v1_live.py`. But that file has been deleted.\n\nCould there be another Python process running outside of OpenClaw? Yes - Leo could be running `vegas_v1_live.py` as a standalone Python script on their own, completely outside of OpenClaw. \n\nThe script would still work since it only depends on yfinance, requests, numpy, and pandas—none of which are OpenClaw specific. So Leo is probably running this manually or via a scheduled task outside of OpenClaw's control, which means I can't stop it from within the system. The Vegas V1 Alpha signal format is distinctive enough that any Python script producing it would need to be the original vegas_v1_live.py file.\n\nNow I'm looking through the agents and teams directories to find who owns this script, since it was previously in the vegas_v1_alpha team that was deleted.\n","thinkingSignature":"b5ceb756a213b75a144f994a6674025d04bc9e54204af014738814794389f5cc"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_oqs9abj0jwpd_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem -Path \"C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\" -Directory -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object Name"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":4299,"output":334,"cacheRead":91840,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":96473,"cost":{"input":0.0012897,"output":0.0004008,"cacheRead":0.0055103999999999995,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0072009}},"sto