{"type":"message","id":"02b5a6c0","parentId":"e5dc0923","timestamp":"2026-05-11T19:54:00.788Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Jo wants to install Qwen 1.5B with automatic installation of any needed plugins/programs. Let me check the image_generate tool capabilities first - it likely has Qwen available. But Jo might want it as a local model for running inference.\n\nActually, this could mean:\n1. Using Qwen 1.5B via an API (like through a configured provider)\n2. Installing Qwen locally for local inference\n\nLet me check what's available for image generation and see if Qwen is available as a model. The image_generate tool has a list action that shows available providers.\n\nAlso, Jo might want to run Qwen locally - which would require ollama or similar. Let me check what's configured and what the options are.\n\n\nI should first check what providers and models are currently available through the image_generate tool's list action, then determine whether Jo is looking for API-based access or a local setup like Ollama.","thinkingSignature":"d5208cbb95e95a1ab787f8c5e537486862bbbd3807b77d38eed8123dd94f0d73"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1n5rl98ymmay_1","name":"image_generate","arguments":{"action":"list"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":106,"output":215,"cacheRead":9845,"cacheWrite":146773,"totalTokens":156939,"cost":{"input":0.0000318,"output":0.000258,"cacheRead":0.0005907,"cacheWrite":0.055039875,"total":0.055920375}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778511706780,"responseId":"0651225eb01edcc0cc68d3701ba5f414"}}
