{"type":"message","id":"2db00c02","parentId":"1649ab9d","timestamp":"2026-05-11T19:54:00.788Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The Qwen model is working! The output is:\n```json\n{\"strategy_name\":\"Tina Architecture Edition\",\"indicator\":{\"RSI\":28,\"Sharpe_Ratio\":1.8},\"params\":{\"MACD_golden_cross\":true,\"foreign_net_buy_signal\":true},\"entry_condition\":{}, \"stop_loss\":0.0}\n```\n\nThis is valid JSON! But it doesn't perfectly match our schema. The `entry_condition` is empty and `stop_loss` is 0.0. The schema wants `entry_condition` to have `operator` and `threshold` fields, and `stop_loss` to be between 0.01-0.50.\n\n\nI notice the strategy name has spaces and special characters that violate the schema requirements, so there's definitely room for improvement. Still, the model is generating valid JSON output and the full setup is functional, so I'll proceed with testing the bridge directly.\n","thinkingSignature":"e2d6332a7762b772d9b592fa3d71d993bbfc584f406f249070eace98a2093e8f"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\n模型活了！快速測試一下 Python bridge：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_nr018f31rdfq_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\\ray; python -c \"\nimport sys; sys.path.insert(0, r'C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\\ray')\nfrom tina_bridge import TinaBridge\nimport json\nbridge = TinaBridge(model='ray-v1')\ndata = 'NVDA | RSI=28 | Sharpe=1.8 | MACD金叉 | 外資淨買'\nresult = bridge.ask_logic('輸出嚴格JSON策略', data)\nprint('Raw:', result)\nparsed = json.loads(result)\nprint('Strategy:', parsed.get('strategy_name'))\nprint('Indicator:', parsed.get('indicator'))\nprint('Stop Loss:', parsed.get('stop_loss'))\n\" 2>&1","timeout":"90"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":387,"output":380,"cacheRead":105472,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":106239,"cost":{"input":0.00011609999999999999,"output":0.00045599999999999997,"cacheRead":0.00632831999999