{"type":"message","id":"90f22c90","parentId":"11e48103","timestamp":"2026-05-11T19:54:00.788Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Jo wants to:\n1. Download the 7B model\n2. Reorganize the division of labor between Ray's local scripts and Qwen\n\nLet me start downloading 7B in the background while thinking about the architecture.\n\nFor the division of labor:\n- 1.5B: Fast, lightweight tasks - used for high-frequency scanning, simple signal validation\n- 7B: Deep analysis, complex strategy proposals, market sentiment, backtest attribution\n\nThe architecture would be:\n- Local Python scripts (us_momentum.py, us_scan_live.py) handle: data fetching, technical indicator calculation, SQLite persistence, Sharpe/MDD math gate checks\n\n\n- Qwen 1.5B handles: quick strategy proposals, simple signal validation, fast context summarization\n- Qwen 7B handles: deep strategy research, complex backtest attribution, market sentiment analysis, multi-factor strategy proposals\n\nNow I'll start the 7B download in the background and then work through the implementation systematically.\n","thinkingSignature":"ddfff384f7065912545837a50a6fc00ea66284ec465bb61c42a573d341922e2d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_a98eb63icd7c_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"background":"true","command":"cmd /c 'cd /d \"C:\\Users\\USER\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\Ollama\" && ollama pull qwen2.5:7b'","yieldMs":"5000"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":653,"output":284,"cacheRead":108544,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":109481,"cost":{"input":0.0001959,"output":0.0003408,"cacheRead":0.006512639999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.007049339999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778526638478,"responseId":"06515cb19e36cd9bf513d23d4f6867e9"}}
