{"type":"message","id":"94bc71f6","parentId":"2c4fd5b1","timestamp":"2026-05-11T19:54:00.788Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me review the other key files and then redesign the system to properly integrate Qwen into the workflow. The key issues I see:\n\n1. `ray_evolution.py` references `log_wisdom` which doesn't exist in `ray_data_center.py`\n2. The scripts don't actually USE Qwen - they compute signals locally but don't feed them to the model\n3. `ray_data_center.py` needs `log_wisdom` for the evolution cycle\n4. The scan scripts need to be unified with a proper brain-driven workflow\n\nLet me plan the fixes:\n1. Add `log_wisdom` table + method to `ray_data_center.py`\n2. Fix `ray_evolution.py` to use `log_wisdom` and work correctly\n\n\n3. Create a unified `ray_scanner.py` that replaces both momentum and live scan and integrates Qwen for idea generation\n4. Create `ray_memory.py` as a proper Qwen-powered memory/context system\n5. Update `ray_engine.py` to be more robust\n\nI'll work through these fixes systematically.\n","thinkingSignature":"8c46ff897649edb1b4664a10353a369664e7695dafc6604a9ea5f2a81969a8a3"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n好，全面檢討。讓我看一下所有腳本：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_islxuiam4kav_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\\ray\\ray_evolution.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":3243,"output":274,"cacheRead":113984,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":117501,"cost":{"input":0.0009729,"output":0.00032879999999999997,"cacheRead":0.006839039999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.008140739999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778526817274,"responseId":"06515d638ea332ff80c65e9f7fb3096d"}}
