{"type":"message","id":"d17d1743","parentId":"93b94660","timestamp":"2026-05-11T19:54:00.788Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see there's a call to `self.db.log_wisdom()` in `ray_evolution.py` but that method doesn't exist in `ray_data_center.py`. I need to add it. Also I need to check `ray_engine.py` for the same missing method.\n\nAlso, `ray_evolution.py` imports `sanitize_llm_output` but that function isn't exported from `ray_nl2code.py`. \n\nAlso, the evolution core doesn't use Qwen at all - it only uses fixed candidate strategies. The whole point of \"evolution\" should be to use Qwen to propose NEW strategies based on market data, not just grid search through fixed candidates.\n\n\nSo I need to add the `log_wisdom()` method to the data center, fix the import of `sanitize_llm_output` from the NL2Code module, and most importantly, integrate Qwen into the evolution loop so it can dynamically propose new strategies instead of relying on a static grid.\n","thinkingSignature":"558744964e14888ef60989583bec9254be37797bd3cc848c687242f31c4a6e8c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_zp305p7xih7m_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\\ray\\ray_nl2code.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2304,"output":240,"cacheRead":117184,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":119728,"cost":{"input":0.0006912,"output":0.000288,"cacheRead":0.00703104,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00801024}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778526828090,"responseId":"06515d6d9a33de6d82eeac8619a54e17"}}
