{"type":"message","id":"299d68ba","parentId":"2b6e5fbb","timestamp":"2026-05-11T19:54:00.788Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The edit tool requires an array of edits with \"newText\" and \"oldText\" fields - the tool has specific parameter names. Let me check - the \"edits\" parameter is an array of objects, each with \"newText\" and \"oldText\". But when I pass as JSON it gets stringified. The tool description says `edits: (edits[].oldText: string, newText: string)`. This means the tool expects the edits parameter to be an array of objects. But the JSON I passed had `\"edits\": \"[...]\"` which is a string. Let me try a different approach - maybe the tool takes individual parameters or maybe I need to use a different parameter format.\n\n\nThe function signature shows `edits` as an array of objects with `oldText` and `newText` properties, so the issue is that I'm passing it as a stringified JSON instead of an actual array. Let me try reformatting without using the edits parameter at all, or perhaps the edit tool works differently than I'm thinking.\n\nActually, looking at the error more carefully - the tool expects `edits` to be a proper array, not a string. When I tried passing it as a JSON string, it failed validation. I think I need to use `exec` instead to run a command that modifies the file directly.\n","thinkingSignature":"4485d7bd9a9b01d17c81c2c74d442cdd0bfd5baf7d7ec324c8eaa215a9d4f224"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gpzqt7e8qsdi_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\\ray; powershell -Command \"(Get-Content ray_brain.py)\" | Select-Object -First 10","timeout":"10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":250,"output":343,"cacheRead":135680,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":136273,"cost":{"input":0.000075,"output":0.0004116,"cacheRead":0.0081408,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0086274}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":177852720