{"type":"message","id":"e3a19f48","parentId":"cc1a5b43","timestamp":"2026-05-11T19:54:00.788Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The DB has tables but no rows. Also there's no WAL file. Let me check the db more carefully and trace what's happening in ray_data_center.py when we do a SELECT COUNT(*).\n\nWait - actually I think I see the issue now. The `get_signal_stats()` method has an issue: when I write to the DB with `log_signal`, it creates a WAL connection. But when reading in `get_signal_stats`, it uses a separate `closing(sqlite3.connect())` context. Since the WAL journal mode was set in `_init_db()`, but when we reconnect for reads, it might be in a different state.\n \nThe database size is 49KB which seems reasonable, but when I check the signals_log table directly with a query, it's empty. Let me try running a simple insert and commit directly to see if I can trace what's happening with the transaction behavior.\n","thinkingSignature":"b67548ea0d226a43c8c8d4e56e971f744e2b335c4dd6ce62f412cdf45d8ebe6b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_lfkoo0wf2u8f_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\\ray; python debug_db.py 2>&1","timeout":"15"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":177,"output":234,"cacheRead":157760,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":158171,"cost":{"input":0.000053099999999999996,"output":0.0002808,"cacheRead":0.0094656,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0097995}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778528027870,"responseId":"0651621dc3b9a46ba2c3feafaeebc3e0"}}
{"type":"message","id":"028ec0bb","parentId":"e3a19f48","timestamp":"2026-05-11T19:54:00.788Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_lfkoo0wf2u8f_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[... 223 more characters truncate"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":158,"aggregated":"DB exists: True\r\nDB size: 49152\r\nWAL exists: False\r\nSHM exists: False\r\nRows: 0\r\nTables: ['signals_log', 'sqlite_sequence', 'positions_log', 'trades_log', 'performance_log', 'backtest_reports', 'sop_versions', 'wisdom_logs']","cwd":"C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\\ray"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778528039051}}
{"type":"message","id":"8ac78b9b","parentId":"028ec0bb","timestamp":"2026-05-11T19:54:00.788Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The db has tables but no rows in signals_log. The issue is that `closing(sqlite3.connect(...))` context manager issue. Let me check the `_conn` method or actually look more closely.\n\nWait, looking at the RayDataCenter code, I don't see a `_conn` method. Let me look at the source again... \n\nActually, looking at the `log_signal` method:\n```python\ndef log_signal(self, symbol: str, source: str, score: float, ...):\n    with closing(sqlite3.connect(self.db_path)) as conn:\n        cur = conn.cursor()\n        cur.execute(\"\"\"INSERT INTO signals_log ... \"\"\", ...)\n\n\n```\n\nReturns `cur.lastrowid`\n\nBut the issue is: when `closing()` context exits, the connection is closed immediately. With WAL mode, uncommitted data might be in the WAL file but not yet flushed to the main database. If `closing()` doesn't properly commit before closing, data could be lost.\n\nActually - `with closing(...)` means the connection is closed when exiting. If `closing()` doesn't have an explicit commit before the `with` block exits... actually in Python, when a connection exits a `with` block, it does NOT automatically commit. SQLite in Python requires explicit `conn.commit()` or `with conn:` (autocommit off by default).\n\nSo the problem is that `closing()` is just calling `conn.close()` at exit without committing, and that means all inserts are being rolled back.\n\nI need to change the context manager to wrap the entire transaction, not just use `closing()`.\n\n```\n","thinkingSignature":"4f960f825642861a7500d175ea5b4a49592a16cb6c3d8e5a7f53d7bd95f5daeb"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_11zwxz48q99z_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\\ray; python -c \"\nimport sqlite3, os\ndb_path = 'ray_wisdom.db'\nconn = sqlite3.connect(db_path)\n# Check autocommit\nprint('Isolation:', conn.isolation_level)\nconn.close()\n# Try explicit commit\nconn2 = sqlite3.connect(db_path)\nconn2.execute('PRAGMA journal_mode=WAL')\ncur = conn2.cursor()\ncur.execute(\\\"INSERT INTO signals_log (symbol, source, score, signal_tag, approved) VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?)\\\", ('TEST', 'debug', 5.0, 'BUY', 0))\nconn2.commit()\nprint('Committed, checking...')\nconn3 = sqlite3.connect(db_path, isolation_level='IMMEDIATE')\nc = conn3.execute('SELECT COUNT(*) FROM signals_log').fetchone()[0]\nprint('Count:', c)\n\"","timeout":"15"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":187,"output":551,"cacheRead":157888,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":158626,"cost":{"input":0.000056099999999999995,"output":0.0006611999999999999,"cacheRead":0.009473279999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01019058}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778528039056,"responseId":"06516229e4e8bee989740f8c81372902"}}
