{"type":"message","id":"1796ffc7","parentId":"7260d322","timestamp":"2026-05-11T19:57:26.971Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see there's `BRAIN_DIVISION.md` - this is a human-created doc that Jo made before the conversation. Let me read it.\n","thinkingSignature":"72b05040680dd6a53d61c003ee37efa5306f7227eff367fc4ecbe71bdc532f98"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5g7tu1tf0tjf_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\\ray\\BRAIN_DIVISION.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":195,"output":71,"cacheRead":120000,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":120266,"cost":{"input":0.0000585,"output":0.0000852,"cacheRead":0.007199999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.007343699999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778529441843,"responseId":"065167a445247bb3e8f97d520f495792"}}
{"type":"message","id":"2efb2da9","parentId":"1796ffc7","timestamp":"2026-05-11T19:57:26.977Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_5g7tu1tf0tjf_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Ray 大腦分工藍圖\n# 本地脚本 vs Qwen 各自的職責邊界\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n層級一：本地 Python（不需要 LLM）\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n負責：客觀計算、數據抓取、數學把關\n\n│ 腳本               │ 職責                              │\n│--------------------│-----------------------------------|\n│ us_momentum.py     │ 1D/5D/20D 動能 + KDJ 計算         │\n│ us_scan_live.py    │ MA20/MA60 + RSI + MACD Hist + KDJ │\n│ ray_data_center.py │ SQLite 持久化（所有數據）           │\n│ ray_engine.py      │ 回測引擎（Sharpe>1.5 / MDD<15%）   │\n│ ray_nl2code.py     │ JSON Schema 驗證（拦截幻覺）        │\n\n摩擦成本：0.15% 美股 / 0.54% 台股\nMath Gate：Sharpe>1.5 + MDD<15% + WinRate>45%\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n層級二：Qwen 1.5B（快速本地推理）\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n負責：即時策略提案、高頻篩選、簡單 JSON 格式化\n\n使用場景：\n  → us_momentum.py 輸出的候選股票，1.5B 快速評估\n  → \"RSI=28, MACD 金叉, Sharpe=1.8\" → 輸出策略 JSON\n  → 每日首次快速掃描（~30 秒內完成）\n  → nl2code.py 格式校驗後的最終確認\n\n速度：CPU 幾秒內回應\n型號：qwen2.5:1.5b（已下載）\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n層級三：Qwen 7B（深度分析）\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n負責：複雜推理、歸因分析、市場情緒、策略進化\n\n使用場景：\n  → RayEvolutionCore 的自主學習（策略提案→回測→迭代）\n  → 回測報告出來後的歸因解讀（為何 Sharpe 高/低？）\n  → 新聞情緒摘要（需要多輪推理）\n  → 投資組合風險評估（多變數複雜判斷）\n  → 進階策略設計（需要突破現有參數框架）\n\n速度：較慢（建議有時間再跑）\n型號：qwen2.5:7b（下載中）\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n分工原則\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n\n✓ 本地脚本做的：\n  - 數據抓取（yfinance）\n  - 指標計算（RSI/KDJ/MACD/EMA）\n  - 數學把關（Sharpe/MDD/WinRate）\n  - 數據持久化（SQLite）\n  - JSON Schema 驗證\n\n✗ Qwen 做的：\n  - 自然語言 → 結構化策略（NL2Code）\n  - 市場情緒理解\n  - 複雜策略優化建議\n  - 歸因分析（為什麼這個策略有效）\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n實際工作流\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n\n1. us_momentum.py → 抓到股票數據 → 計算指標\n2. ray_engine.py → 跑 Sharpe/MDD 把關 → 通過的信號進 SQLite\n3. Qwen 1.5B → 把通過的信號轉成策略 JSON → 寫入 signals_log\n4. Qwen 7B → 每日深度複習（進化學習）→ 更新 backtest_reports\n\n這樣每個層級做自己最擅長的事，1.5B 負責快，7B 負責準。"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1778529446977}}
{"type":"message","id":"1b21265a","parentId":"2efb2da9","timestamp":"2026-05-11T19:57:42.856Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to increase the proportion of local Qwen usage and reduce MiniMax token costs. Looking at the system configuration, the current setup is:\n\n- MiniMax (cloud): current default model for OpenClaw\n- Qwen 1.5B (local): ray-v1 model, fast but lower reasoning quality\n- Qwen 7B (local, in progress): deep analysis\n\nTo reduce MiniMax token costs and increase local Qwen usage, I need to understand what tools/configs are available in OpenClaw. Since I don't have access to the gateway config, I should use the gateway tool's config schema lookup to understand what's available.\n\nLet me check the OpenClaw docs for model configuration.\n\n\nMy primary lever is the `default_model` in the agent config which determines what OpenClaw uses for its own reasoning and responses. For local Qwen to handle user requests directly, I'd need to spawn it as a sub-agent or configure OpenClaw to route to it, but the gateway config approach isn't something I can explore without access to the gateway tool.\n\nLooking at the math: if I can route 70-80% of user requests through local Qwen instead of MiniMax, that's roughly $0.002 per message in savings. The practical approach is to be more selective about when I actually invoke the cloud model versus using cached results or handling requests directly with local resources.\n\nSo I should be more intentional about when I invoke MiniMax - only for genuine reasoning, complex analysis, or multi-step orchestration that local Qwen can't handle. For straightforward questions, fact lookups, or anything that fits the cached context, I should lean on local processing instead. Local Qwen only for genuinely hard multi-step problems (planning, complex logic)\n2. For everything else: try local first (ray-v1), but if it fails or times out, fall back to MiniMax\n3. Keep MiniMax only for fallback\n\nThe `session_status` tool has a `model` parameter that can override the default. So I should be more intentional: only use MiniMax when I truly need its reasoning capabilities, otherwise rely on local Qwen for most requests.\n","thinkingSignature":"12c86e2dd05dc054387df55c72c857bde15f0cb8c6c263c641ca89c357d264bb"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_cid4azholrl9_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"dir \"C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\\ray\" /b 2>nul","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":838,"output":495,"cacheRead":120192,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":121525,"cost":{"input":0.0002514,"output":0.000594,"cacheRead":0.007211519999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.008056919999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778529446980,"responseId":"065167a95e6913613e83e69ee052ba75"}}
